data.Clinical History:
Mr. U. Srinivas Rao and Mrs. U. Sri Lakshmi were presented with secondary infertility. They have had a
history of one biochemical pregnancy and 6 failed IUI cycles. Mr. Srinivas Rao has been diagnosed with
Grade III varicocele. Semen analysis was indicative of Oligozoospermia. Whole Exome sequencing in couple 
(done at Anderson Diagnostics and Labs) was indicative of Mr. Srinivas Rao to be carrier of uncertain 
significance variant in RYR1: c.6731G>A, ALMS1: c.3477G>T, NLRP7: c.2396A>G gene and Mrs. U. Sri 
Lakshmi carrier of ALMS1 : c.4249C>T ; NLRP7 : c.448G>A. Additionally, both of them are carriers of 
common uncertain significant variants in the TOP3A: c.2779G>T; GCGR: c.307G>A and SYNE1:c.21952G>A. 
Donor of Mrs. U. Sri Lakshmi (PS) is a comprehensive oocyte donor and has been evaluated for carrier status 
of pathogenic variations.

data.Clinical History: Mr. Wasim Hyder and Mrs. Fatima Jannath are a third-degree consanguineous couple. Their first pregnancy was miscarried at 7 weeks GA. Their second pregnancy's USG at 10 weeks GA was indicative of absent fetal cardiac activity. FISH analysis of chr 13,18,21,x and y in product  of conception was negative. Male partner's maternal aunt's son has hearing loss and intellectual disability. Mr. Wasim Hyder and Mrs. Fatima Jannath has been evaluated for carrier status of pathogenic variations.
